# External Binary Plugin System

## Goal
Allow event getters and status setters to be compiled as separate binaries,
discoverable from `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/status/bin/`. Modeled after Docker/kubectl
plugin conventions. JSON over stdin/stdout protocol.

## Convention
- Getter plugins: `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/status/bin/status-getter-<name>`
- Setter plugins: `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/status/bin/status-setter-<name>`

## Protocol
All communication is JSON over stdin/stdout, one subprocess invocation per call.

### Discovery (`--metadata`)
Binary receives no stdin; prints JSON to stdout:
```json
{
  "name": "google-calendar",
  "type": "getter",
  "min_interval": "1m",
  "param_specs": [{"name": "calendar_id", "description": "...", "required": true, "type": "string"}]
}
```

### GetEvents (`--get-events`)
stdin:  `{"params": {"key": "value"}}`
stdout: `{"events": [...], "error": "optional"}`

### SetStatus (`--set-status`)
stdin:  `{"params": {"key": "value"}}`
stdout: `{"skipped": false, "response": "ok", "error": "optional"}`

